        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="342" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93/12–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-20">December 20,
                            1946</date>.<lb/>[Received December 20—7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2140. Wang Ping-nan, Communist spokesman at Nanking, said [on] 19th that Yenan
                    would officially reply to Truman’s China statement. Told correspondents his
                    personal views were: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“There is urgent need at the present moment for true peace, democracy and
                            unity. Only a peaceful China can contribute to world peace. If United
                            States is sincere in her desire to promote peace in China, then she must
                            stop immediately all unilateral assistance to the Kuomintang and
                            withdraw completely all American troops from China. If she does that, I
                            believe she would be of great help in terminating China’s civil
                            war.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
